Part 1: Install Visual Studio Code
Step 1: Download VS Code
Visit: https://code.visualstudio.com/
Click Download according to your operating system (Windows/macOS/Linux).
Step 2: Install VS Code
Run the installer.
Click Next.
Accept the License Agreement.
Click Next until the Select Additional Tasks screen.
Check:
✅ Add "Open with Code" action
✅ Add to PATH
✅ Register Code as an editor
Click Install.
Click Finish.
Step 3: Open VS Code

Verify that VS Code opens successfully.

Part 2: Install Python Extension
Open VS Code.
Click the Extensions icon (Ctrl + Shift + X).
Search for Python.
Install the Python extension published by Microsoft.
Part 3: Install Git
Windows
Visit: https://git-scm.com/downloads
Download Git for Windows.
Run the installer.
Keep the default settings (or choose VS Code as the default editor).
Click Install.
Click Finish.
macOS

Open Terminal and run:

xcode-select --install

Verify installation:

git --version
Part 4: Create a GitHub Account
Visit https://github.com
Click Sign Up.
Enter:
Email Address
Username
Password
Verify your email.
Complete the setup.
Part 5: Configure Git

Open the VS Code Terminal.

git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "your@email.com"

Verify:

git config --list
Part 6: Verify Installation
Check Python
python --version

or (macOS)

python3 --version
Check Git
git --version
